article.headline: Alabama 81, Missouri St. 73
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Richard Hendrix had 30 points and nine rebounds Saturday night and Alonzo Gee scored 15 of his 18 points in the second half as Alabama overcame an eight-point second half deficit for an 81-73 victory against Missouri State at the Las Vegas Holiday Classic. Alabama plays Iowa State, which beat Purdue later Saturday, in Sunday's tournament championship game. Missouri State made seven of its first eight shots in the second half, including 3-pointers from Ryan Jehle and Shane Laurie, to open a 49-41 lead with 14:23 to play, but the Bears didn't have an answer for the 6-foot-9, 255 pound Hendrix, who made 13-of-15 field goals and helped Alabama rally for a 58-56 lead with 8:08 left. Gee keyed the comeback with three straight baskets. The teams traded points until the final two minutes when Gee had a put-back dunk on a Hendrix miss for a 72-71 Alabama lead. The Crimson Tide's Mykal Riley then hit a 3-pointer with 51 seconds to play to extend the lead to five. Alabama (8-3) shot 75 percent and scored 50 points in the second half. The Tide trailed by as many as eight in the first half, but held Missouri State without a field goal for seven minutes in a 10-1 run to take a 19-18 lead with 7:47 to play in the half. Hendrix keyed the outburst with four of his 12 first-half points, while Riley connected on a 3-pointer and Mikhail Torrance made a pair of uncontested lay-ups. Riley scored 13 for the Tide and Torrance added 10. Missouri State (7-4) got 13 points apiece from Laurie and Chris Cooks.
